label.value: Paracervical Route of Administration

value.value: Administration of medication to the side of the cervix.

label.value: Paravertebral Route of Administration

value.value: Injection of a veterinary medicinal product along the spinal column of animals.

label.value: Per

value.value: For each, generally denoting a ratio.

label.value: Diffuse Lipomatosis

value.value: A neoplastic process characterized by a diffuse poorly circumscribed overgrowth of adipose tissue.  It has been associated with several genetic disorders and different clinical conditions such as liver disease, excessive alcohol intake, adrenocortical steroid therapy, and antiretroviral therapy.

label.value: Administration via Percutaneous Gastrostomy
Peribulbar Route of Administration

value.value: Administration of medication under the globe of the eye.

label.value: Periosteal Route of Administration

value.value: Administration to periosteum, the thick, fibrous membrane covering the entire surface of a bone except its articular cartilage and the areas where it attaches to tendons and ligaments.

label.value: Peritendinous Route of Administration

value.value: Administration of medication around the tendon.

label.value: Periurethral Route of Administration

value.value: Administration of a drug within the tissues surrounding the urethra.

label.value: Picomole

value.value: A unit of amount of substance equal to a trillionth (10E-12) of a mole.

label.value: Put

value.value: Cause to be in a certain state, relationship, or location.

label.value: CDISC SDTM Laboratory Test Code Terminology

value.value: A terminology set that includes concepts contained in the CDISC laboratory test codelist.

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Atypical Lipomatous Tumor/Well Differentiated Liposarcoma

value.value: A locally aggressive mesenchymal neoplasm composed either entirely or partly of an adipocytic proliferation showing at least focal nuclear atypia in both adipocytes and stromal cells. "Atypical lipomatous tumor" and "well-differentiated liposarcoma" are synonyms describing lesions that are morphologically and genetically identical. Amplification of MDM2 and/or CDK4 is almost always present. (WHO 2020)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pTis TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with tumor restricted to any one subsite, with or without bony invasion. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with tumor invading two subsites in a single region or extending to involve an adjacent region within the nasoethmoidal complex, with or without bony invasion. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pT3 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with tumor invading the medial wall or floor of the orbit, maxillary sinus, palate, or cribriform plate. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pT4a TNM Finding v6

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with tumor invading any of the following: anterior orbital contents, skin of nose or cheek, minimal extension to anterior cranial fossa, pterygoid plates, sphenoid or frontal sinuses. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pT4b TNM Finding v6

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with tumor invading any of the following: orbital apex, dura, brain, middle cranial fossa, cranial nerves other than the maxillary division of the trigeminal nerve, nasopharynx, or clivus. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Postprandial
Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pM0 TNM Finding

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with no distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pMX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer in which distant metastasis cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Puff Dosing Unit

value.value: A dosing unit equal to the amount of active ingredient(s) contained in a puff.

label.value: Push

value.value: The act of applying force in order to move something away.

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with no metastasis to regional lymph nodes. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with metastasis to a single ipsilateral lymph node, 3 cm or less in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pN2a TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with metastasis to a single ipsilateral lymph node, more than 3 cm, but not more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pN2b TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with metastasis in multiple ipsilateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pN2c TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with metastasis in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer with metastasis in a lymph node, more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Nasal Cavity and Ethmoid Sinus Cancer pNX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Nasal cavity and ethmoid sinus cancer in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Rapidly

value.value: Acting or occurring in a brief period of time.

label.value: Sclerosing Atypical Lipomatous Tumor/Well Differentiated Liposarcoma

value.value: An atypical lipomatous tumor/well differentiated liposarcoma characterized by the presence of bizarre hyperchromatic stromal cells and rare multivacuolated lipoblasts within a fibrous stroma.

label.value: Regimen Used to Treat Cervical Carcinoma

value.value: Any regimen that can be used for the treatment of cervical carcinoma.

label.value: Cisplatin/Topotecan Regimen

value.value: A regimen consisting of cisplatin and topotecan used for the treatment of advanced-stage and recurrent cervical cancer.

label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer Pathologic TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of major salivary gland cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system.

label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of major salivary gland cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of major salivary gland cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Right and Left
Clean

value.value: The action of removing dirt, filth, or unwanted substances from.

label.value: Wash

value.value: Cleanse with a cleaning agent, such as soap, and water.

label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of major salivary gland cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer pTX TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Major salivary gland cancer in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Inflammatory Atypical Lipomatous Tumor/Well Differentiated Liposarcoma

value.value: A rare morphologic variant of atypical lipomatous tumor/well differentiated liposarcoma occurring most often in the retroperitoneum. It is characterized by the presence of a predominant chronic inflammatory infiltrate.

label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer pT0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Major salivary gland cancer with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer pT1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Major salivary gland cancer with tumor 2 cm or less in greatest dimension without extraparenchymal extension. Extraparenchymal extension is clinical or macroscopic evidence of invasion of soft tissues. Microscopic evidence alone does not constitute extraparenchymal extension for classification purposes. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Major Salivary Gland Cancer pT2 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Major salivary gland cancer with tumor more than 2 cm, but not more than 4 cm in greatest dimension without extraparenchymal extension. Extraparenchymal extension is clinical or macroscopic evidence of invasion of soft tissues. Microscopic evidence alone does not constitute extraparenchymal extension for classification purposes. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)
